cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the use of Deep Neural Networks for Computer Vision tasks and the need for explainability of their predictions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of explainers and their properties, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential biases and unfairness in decision-making algorithms, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
